3121
01:44:17,684 --> 01:44:18,652
Who have been very successful

3122
01:44:18,885 --> 01:44:20,654
Right especially at Anthropic this company

3123
01:44:22,089 --> 01:44:23,890
When many people describe this generation of AI

3124
01:44:23,890 --> 01:44:24,992
They all say it's a black box

3125
01:44:26,093 --> 01:44:27,294
Can you use a scientific perspective

3126
01:44:27,294 --> 01:44:28,929
To understand this black box

3127
01:44:28,929 --> 01:44:30,597
The operating principles of artificial intelligence

3128
01:44:30,597 --> 01:44:32,799
I think

3129
01:44:33,767 --> 01:44:35,369
Everything in this world is a black box

3130
01:44:36,370 --> 01:44:39,973
Like even physics

3131
01:44:39,973 --> 01:44:41,508
Something everyone thinks they understand

3132
01:44:41,508 --> 01:44:44,711
Actually doesn't really have

3133
01:44:44,711 --> 01:44:47,080
An understanding from its microscopic behavior

3134
01:44:47,080 --> 01:44:49,716
All the way to macroscopic manifestations

3135
01:44:50,450 --> 01:44:52,319
Like whether it's quantum mechanics

3136
01:44:52,319 --> 01:44:52,886
Or quantum field theory

3137
01:44:52,886 --> 01:44:55,322
They all describe behavior at that energy scale

3138
01:44:55,455 --> 01:44:56,923
Essentially the system is still a black box

3139
01:44:56,923 --> 01:44:58,825
You still don't know at its most microscopic level

3140
01:44:58,825 --> 01:44:59,893
What kind of dynamics

3141
01:45:00,460 --> 01:45:01,228
AI is the same

3142
01:45:01,228 --> 01:45:02,562
Whether it's a black box or not

3143
01:45:02,562 --> 01:45:03,764
Is actually all relative

3144
01:45:03,930 --> 01:45:06,667
We indeed don't understand language models to the level of

3145
01:45:07,968 --> 01:45:09,436
Neurosurgery-level precision

3146
01:45:09,436 --> 01:45:11,538
It's not that I understand this behavior

3147
01:45:11,538 --> 01:45:12,272
To the extent of

3148
01:45:12,272 --> 01:45:15,475
Saying this behavior is caused by which neuron

3149
01:45:15,475 --> 01:45:18,345
Which artificial neuron's which activation

3150
01:45:18,345 --> 01:45:19,279
Producing this behavior

3151
01:45:19,713 --> 01:45:21,515
We don't have that

3152
01:45:21,515 --> 01:45:22,449
Haven't reached that level of understanding

3153
01:45:22,449 --> 01:45:24,351
Except in some very sparse

3154
01:45:24,351 --> 01:45:26,253
Very small networks

3155
01:45:26,253 --> 01:45:27,087
Like Anthropic

3156
01:45:27,087 --> 01:45:28,989
Has this so-called Interpretability

3157
01:45:28,989 --> 01:45:29,489
Interpretability team

3158
01:45:29,489 --> 01:45:30,857
They might do some similar work

3159
01:45:30,857 --> 01:45:33,293
But in practically usable language models

3160
01:45:33,293 --> 01:45:34,628
We haven't reached such understanding

3161
01:45:34,828 --> 01:45:36,697
But it doesn't mean we have no understanding at all

3162
01:45:37,297 --> 01:45:38,265
For example Scaling Law

3163
01:45:38,265 --> 01:45:41,802
It describes how models at that scale

3164
01:45:41,802 --> 01:45:47,407
With model size and data improve in perplexity

3165
01:45:47,407 --> 01:45:50,544
Under this metric get better and better

3166
01:45:50,544 --> 01:45:53,146
Mm-hmm so you say there's no understanding at all

3167
01:45:53,146 --> 01:45:54,081
Well if

3168
01:45:54,081 --> 01:45:54,481
Scaling Law

3169
01:45:54,481 --> 01:45:56,483
Doesn't count as a small part of understanding

3170
01:45:56,483 --> 01:45:57,484
Then can we also say

3171
01:45:57,484 --> 01:45:58,919
We actually don't understand this world at all either

3172
01:45:58,919 --> 01:46:00,520
This world is also a complete black box

3173
01:46:01,488 --> 01:46:04,725
So Scaling Law is a scientific law

3174
01:46:05,058 --> 01:46:06,293
It's an empirical law

3175
01:46:06,493 --> 01:46:07,527
An empirical law

3176
01:46:07,527 --> 01:46:08,027
Right

3177
01:46:08,128 --> 01:46:09,696
But

3178
01:46:09,896 --> 01:46:11,798
The boundary between empirical laws and scientific laws

3179
01:46:11,798 --> 01:46:13,633
is quite blurry

3180
01:46:14,334 --> 01:46:16,470
For example

3181
01:46:17,404 --> 01:46:19,439
If we look back at these thermodynamic

3182
01:46:19,439 --> 01:46:21,308
various different laws

3183
01:46:21,308 --> 01:46:22,609
The first law, the second law

3184
01:46:22,609 --> 01:46:23,744
The Clapeyron equation and whatnot

3185
01:46:23,744 --> 01:46:24,144
all this messy stuff

3186
01:46:24,144 --> 01:46:26,747
When they were first discovered

3187
01:46:26,747 --> 01:46:27,748
they were also empirical laws

3188
01:46:28,648 --> 01:46:29,549
It's just that later on

3189
01:46:29,549 --> 01:46:30,417
as time went by

3190
01:46:30,417 --> 01:46:32,185
we gradually understood their microscopic mechanisms

3191
01:46:32,185 --> 01:46:33,954
Then they might have become scientific laws

3192
01:46:34,421 --> 01:46:36,390
Right, I think maybe something like Scaling Law

3193
01:46:36,390 --> 01:46:38,225
or things like that

3194
01:46:38,225 --> 01:46:40,827
Right now it's definitely still very impressive

3195
01:46:41,027 --> 01:46:44,531
But in the future, when the technology becomes more fixed

3196
01:46:44,531 --> 01:46:46,266
and people start to understand it more and more

3197
01:46:46,266 --> 01:46:47,167
the microscopic process

3198
01:46:47,167 --> 01:46:48,969
will it become a scientific law

3199
01:46:48,969 --> 01:46:51,138
